Learn Basic Python
------------------
1. Download from Github:
    > cd work                      # change directory to ~/work
    > mkdir LearnPython            # create a new directory called LearnPython
    > cd LearnPython               # change directory to ~/work/LearnPython
    > git clone https://github.com/rajathkmp/Python-Lectures.git
                                   # Read examples from Github repository

2. Use ipython/jupyter to go over examples
    > cd work/LearnPython/Python-Lectures
    > jupyter notebook             # start a Jupyter notebook to work on

    In browser, click 01.ipython
    Click Run button to go thru the example

    Use 02.ipython to be familiar with basic python syntax

3. Data Structures
    List: Go thru 03.ipython to learn "LIST"
    String: Go thru 04.ipython to learn "STRING"
    Control structure: Go thru 05.ipython to learn if-else, for loops

4. Write a iPython/Jupyter program to interpret date:
   Input is a string of various date formats, output year/month/day in separate line. 
   For example:
       my_program May-21-1997
    Or my_program 05/21/1997
   should all produce:
       Year: 1997
       Month: May
       Day: 21
   (1) Write your own date_translator
   (2) Use datetime library:
       from datetime import datetime
       datetime.strptime('Jan-01-2000', '%b-%d-%Y')

5. Learn functions/classes
   Go thru 06.ipython and 07.ipython to learn how to write functions and classes

6. Learn Dictionary
   1) Use jupyter to go thru dictionaries.ipynb example
   2) Reimplement date_interpreter program by adding translation from word month to number month
      using dictionaries.


